children.subject: I will just toss in that I think Data8 was a perfect intro to stats/DS and was a really great class. I learned a lot and I think its one of the best classes I've taken here (taken 188, 100, will take 189 in the Spring)

history.content: Data8 is a good intro. If you think you are sufficiently strong in math, CS70 and some linear algebra will be enough to get you through 188, 189 at the very least.

I didn't take AP stats in high school so I'm wondering if an intro stats course is necessary, or CS70 + EE126 will suffice.

I plan to take CS 188, CS 189, CS 280 and audit the online materials for CS 287 and CS 294 RL.

Thanks in advance.
